description.narrative: Multiple innovative efforts are ongoing in South Africa to reduce new HIV infections among adolescent girls and young women aged 15-24. Between 2014 and 2019, there was a decline of about 39 per cent in new infections among adolescent girls and young women (15 – 24 years). While this positive trend constitutes an encouraging finding, it is important to increase uptake of HIV testing and counselling by adolescents and to give appropriate and successful linkage to prevention, treatment and care services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/01/2020
